06:19.980 --> 06:23.664
And I'm speaking different, you know, it's coming from a different perspective now.

06:24.045 --> 06:33.977
Because as I was saying yesterday, the view from 2026 as we look into this future is completely different than it was in 1996 when Rick and I came here.

06:34.337 --> 06:44.850
And in 1926, when mass started, we are entering into a complex and very broken world.

06:45.282 --> 06:49.667
And it has to be that the church understands why it's here and what it's here for.

06:49.967 --> 06:57.877
We're not called to be in feedback loops that tell us that this is our enemy and these are the good people and these are the bad people.

06:58.217 --> 07:03.984
No, we're called to be the people of God who are representing Jesus Christ in our district.

07:04.044 --> 07:07.187
So anyway, so that's all my preambles.

07:07.267 --> 07:12.914
But have you ever felt like you're on automatic pilot as a Christian?

07:13.026 --> 07:14.668
You know, I have, I have a lot.

07:15.069 --> 07:35.514
In fact, sometimes I've suddenly realized that I've been on automatic pilot for a while and I've been doing all the right things out of habit and because I know it's right and because it's my lifestyle and these are my friends and this is where I hang out with them but I'm not functioning out of a rich, strong, daily relationship with Jesus Christ.

07:36.054 --> 07:42.162
And if I look at it closely, I see those are the times that I excuse the fact and listen to me

07:42.530 --> 08:10.738
Those are the times when I excuse the fact that I'm not forgiving people that I'm upset with and I'm not acknowledging when I'm wrong and I'm gossiping and I've become a partner in allowing division to damage the work of the Lord and maybe I'm watching something that I don't really want Jesus to watch with me and I'm trying to get away with doing something that I know is wrong.

08:11.618 --> 08:20.553
And when that happens, what it means is sometimes I've lost the current of the water of life that washes those wrong things away.

08:21.595 --> 08:29.448
And the reason that that happens is because I have lost understanding of the connection to Jesus Christ and what that does.

08:29.848 --> 08:33.995
Revelation 21 verse 6 says, he said to me, it's done.

08:34.035 --> 08:35.698
That means I don't have to

08:35.874 --> 08:38.537
do more stuff to make it be done because it is done.

08:39.038 --> 08:39.639
It is done.

08:39.679 --> 08:42.723
I am the alpha and the omega, the beginning and the end.

08:42.743 --> 08:47.189
To him who is thirsty, I will give to drink without cost.

08:47.850 --> 08:53.016
Some of us are broke, but it's not going to make any difference to get the water of life.

08:53.097 --> 09:01.688
Some of us are really rich, but that doesn't make any difference to get the water of life because it says without cost from the spring of the water of life.

09:01.748 --> 09:03.410
So being a recipient

09:03.490 --> 09:17.809
and a source of the water of life is always a direct result of time spent with Jesus and having it wash away all the gunk that is in me because the washing away is current with me.

09:17.829 --> 09:24.658
And he says it himself, John 414, Jesus says, but whoever drinks the water I give him will never thirst.

09:25.090 --> 09:28.876
anybody thirsty out there for something more than what we've got right now.

09:29.436 --> 09:35.566
Indeed, the water I give him will become in him a fountain, springing up unto eternal life.

09:35.866 --> 09:47.644
And this is the thing that's really amazing about that because, you know, when we were in the prayer meeting and then again this morning when Nikki was worship leading, she was speaking about fountains and she didn't know I was speaking about fountains.

09:47.964 --> 09:51.890
And I hadn't said to anybody, I'm talking about fountains or the water of life,

09:51.970 --> 09:58.039
But it was something that the Holy Spirit is doing because it's important for us as a people to understand that right now.

09:58.479 --> 10:16.946
John chapter 7, verse 37 and 38, on the last and greatest day of the feast, Jesus stood and said in a loud voice, if anyone is thirsty, if anyone is thirsty, let him come to me and drink

10:17.410 --> 10:24.758
Whoever believes in me, as the scripture has said, out of his innermost being will flow rivers of living water.

10:25.840 --> 10:27.381
So there's two criteria here.

10:27.822 --> 10:29.724
There's thirst and there's belief.

10:30.545 --> 10:35.791
You know what it is to suddenly be hydrated, but you didn't know it until you had a drink of water.

10:35.811 --> 10:44.241
And then you found yourself drinking the entire glass down because you were dehydrated, but we often do not recognize the signs of dehydration.

10:44.661 --> 10:45.362
Sometimes

10:45.474 --> 10:52.184
A full glass of water is a remedy for a headache because a headache is a sign of being dehydrated.

10:52.624 --> 11:00.776
And so the source of our spiritual refreshment is our ongoing connection with Jesus Christ.

11:01.137 --> 11:04.241
But the choice to connect has to be now.

11:05.002 --> 11:13.234
It can't be yesterday or last week or last year when I did a whole lot of work with the Lord and that order carry me through from now.

11:13.986 --> 11:19.734
Only Jesus can quench spiritual dehydration, but we forget that.

11:19.874 --> 11:27.224
And listen to me, we think that what we do in our Christian life is our Christian life.

11:28.045 --> 11:30.288
And that's a bigger problem than we realize.

11:31.309 --> 11:35.815
Jeremiah chapter two, verse 13, this is God speaking to the people.

11:35.855 --> 11:38.198
This is Jehovah God.

11:38.759 --> 11:43.986
My people have committed two sins, not two actually mistakes, but sins.

11:44.322 --> 11:50.802
They have forsaken me, the spring of living water, and they have dug their own systems.

11:50.946 --> 11:53.488
broken systems that cannot hold water.

11:53.889 --> 12:03.078
And it's amazing to me how the Old and the New Testament come together because even in the Old Testament, here is God referring to himself as a spring of living water.

12:03.338 --> 12:04.319
I think that's amazing.

12:04.739 --> 12:06.881
But he's saying the problem is twofold.

12:07.282 --> 12:09.884
First, they've forsaken this spring of living water.

12:10.205 --> 12:16.130
And second is that they're developing something that's kind of like a counterfeit or a facsimile.

12:16.471 --> 12:20.114
And this is the point, a facsimile is different from a well.

12:22.466 --> 12:28.695
Yeah, can we go back to the system and the well together, the diagram?

12:29.796 --> 12:30.978
Yes.

12:31.038 --> 12:34.923
This is the point that a system is different from a well.

12:35.244 --> 12:41.132
A system is a bottle-shaped tank that's cut into rock or it's hewn from masonry.

12:41.513 --> 12:46.840
It's about 100 foot, can go up to 100 foot deep and it's plastered and it's concreted.

12:46.880 --> 12:51.186
It's a tank for still water that's been collected

12:52.194 --> 12:53.196
from the outside.

12:53.256 --> 12:59.405
Basically, it's been fed by surface water, drainage, roof drainage, gutters and pipes catching rain, et cetera.

12:59.725 --> 13:02.670
And so it flows in and then it gets bucketed out.

13:03.331 --> 13:09.080
And they lived, and keep that up for a little while, actually, they lived in the desert where the water was precious.

13:09.280 --> 13:10.322
It was a desert land.

13:10.602 --> 13:12.184
The summers were long and dry.

13:12.565 --> 13:15.449
There were very little rainfall and very few springs.

13:16.050 --> 13:18.514
Some people had private systems in their backyard.

13:18.690 --> 13:20.392
back gardens to catch the water.

13:20.833 --> 13:22.655
And towns had huge public ones.

13:23.096 --> 13:27.943
In fact, in Jerusalem, there was one that held between two and three million gallons of water.

13:28.544 --> 13:35.854
But what happened was the water comes in from the outside and impurities are washed in as well as the water.

13:36.014 --> 13:40.480
And so they're both, you know, it's water, but it's not pure water.

13:41.021 --> 13:44.025
And so the tank's got to be cleaned regularly.

13:44.125 --> 13:45.227
So that's a bit of a problem.

13:45.727 --> 13:47.570
Then the tanks break.

13:47.682 --> 13:49.024
And that's the bigger problem.

13:49.044 --> 13:53.492
And it's a tragedy when the tank breaks because all the water is lost.

13:53.552 --> 13:59.481
Not only does it leak out, but any incoming water as well is immediately lost into the ground.

13:59.882 --> 14:07.154
And it leaves on a murky, muddy sediment at the bottom of the cistern where rats and snakes lived.

14:07.458 --> 14:10.343
Broken systems were used as prisons.

14:10.484 --> 14:18.939
In fact, if you read your Bible, both Joseph and Jeremiah, as well as many other people, were imprisoned in this kind of broken system.

14:19.040 --> 14:19.841
And they're down there.

14:20.142 --> 14:21.304
There is no way out.

14:21.344 --> 14:22.546
The pictures that I

14:22.722 --> 14:26.365
that I have of the systems do not give an adequate understanding.

14:26.406 --> 14:37.636
In fact, in the book of Jeremiah, it talks about the fact that they had to throw down ropes and rags for him to put under his arms and then tie the ropes around and drag him back out.

14:37.696 --> 14:41.680
There was no way out for somebody who was imprisoned in a system.

14:41.720 --> 14:45.224
They would have died there, had not their captives changed their mind.

14:46.064 --> 14:47.226
So this is my question.

14:48.847 --> 14:51.890
How many people are prisoners

14:52.130 --> 14:54.093
insistence of their own making.

14:55.235 --> 15:10.196
Good Christian people who don't realize how dehydrated they've become, not understanding that they've lost the desire or the belief, the thirst to keep coming back to Jesus to drink the living water.

15:11.038 --> 15:16.786
We build containers of our lifestyle and our values and our good behavior.

15:17.122 --> 15:23.528
And we think that that's the same as a living and vital relationship with God who gave us his life.

15:24.689 --> 15:27.152
It's not too much work to fill it up, actually.

15:27.512 --> 15:39.964
It flows in from the outside through relationships and preaching and podcasts and the books we read and the feedback loop that we're in and the things that we learned back in the day.

15:40.044 --> 15:46.610
But what we don't realize is that it's just cracked and it just keeps flowing away.

15:46.754 --> 15:48.317
and life isn't there in us.

15:48.397 --> 15:50.480
See, a well is very different.

15:51.081 --> 15:53.005
A well puts in the effort.

15:53.125 --> 16:00.458
A well has a drawers water up from underneath springs in the ground where nobody can see.

16:00.498 --> 16:05.827
Nobody can see where that water is down there, but the well is drawing it up all the time.

16:06.187 --> 16:12.338
And so therefore, because of the way a well functions, unless somebody chucks something in it, the water is always pure.

16:12.866 --> 16:14.548
It's just an amazing thing.

16:14.628 --> 16:27.246
And so through relationship with Jesus Christ, we've all been given the capacity for living water to become in us a fountain, springing up to eternal life.

16:27.266 --> 16:28.548
It starts as a well.

16:28.588 --> 16:36.178
Psalm chapter 1 talks about godly people being like trees planted by water, not relying on the rain, but putting in the effort

16:36.290 --> 16:41.837
to draw deeply from the water source that's under the ground so the tree is healthy and strong.

16:42.217 --> 16:49.446
And the idea is to draw the living water every day, all the time, through the root system as we're connected to Jesus Christ.

16:49.486 --> 17:02.702
So what happens spiritually is that a miracle takes place as that well transforms because in us, it can become a fountain, not only watering us, but quenching the thirst of the people around us.

17:03.263 --> 17:05.746
And this is the point, fountains and rivers

17:05.826 --> 17:07.168
cannot be contained.

17:07.608 --> 17:10.932
The water pours out as it's drawn in.

17:10.992 --> 17:15.358
It's a transference of living waters into the thirsty person.

17:15.698 --> 17:17.480
John chapter seven, verses 37, 38.

17:17.580 --> 17:23.047
If anyone firsts, it's so easy to connect with the source.

17:23.768 --> 17:26.311
The only criterion is first.

17:27.633 --> 17:35.442
It is amazingly easy to disconnect as well without even realizing, I have done it more times than I can possibly count.

17:36.194 --> 17:43.047
we have such a tendency to put things in boxes, including the things that the Lord gave us absolutely freely.

17:43.428 --> 17:55.410
It's human nature to try and bottle living water in our own container so that it will save us time from continually pursuing this relationship every day.

17:55.714 --> 17:56.395
with Jesus.

17:56.495 --> 18:02.968
And so Isaiah chapter 12 verse 3 says, therefore with joy shall you draw water out of the wells of salvation.

18:03.389 --> 18:05.493
Draw is a doing word.

18:05.613 --> 18:06.394
It's a verb.

18:06.454 --> 18:11.364
It requires effort to draw water, especially if we're going to do it with joy.

18:11.404 --> 18:14.690
Because often we don't do it with joy in any way at all.

18:14.890 --> 18:16.754
We do it with

18:16.994 --> 18:23.904
miserableness and complaining and irritation and why is it always me and any number of other things.

18:24.365 --> 18:27.930
But we think to ourselves, I'll draw enough to last me for a while.

18:27.950 --> 18:29.853
So I won't have to keep going back all the time.

18:30.574 --> 18:32.978
I'll make a little container to last me for a while.

18:34.300 --> 18:43.954
I'll have a lifestyle, a set of values, my work in the church or in the organization that I'm part of, my ministry so that

18:44.258 --> 18:47.782
I can have a rest from working on this relationship all the time.

18:48.322 --> 18:49.564
Jesus is cool with that.

18:50.044 --> 18:51.626
He's cool with that, he understands.

18:52.307 --> 18:59.955
Listen, resting from a relationship with God has the same effect as taking a rest from a relationship with the person that you're married.

19:01.998 --> 19:07.864
You gradually lose the closeness and you end up with only the format, the form work.

19:07.884 --> 19:09.586
And every married couple

19:09.666 --> 19:17.835
has to work against being happy families on the outside and hollow on the inside, and that can happen to any marriage or any relationship.

19:18.576 --> 19:38.258
But by definition of that scripture in Jeremiah, our systems represent our loss of connection with God when other things crowd in, our ministry description, our rights and responsibilities, the way we want to be seen by all the people around us, our need to be acknowledged, our fear of losing comfort,

19:38.562 --> 19:52.223
Those things so easily become our system, and for a while they seem to serve the purpose, but God loves us too much to allow us to continually get away with a facade disguised as a relationship with Him.

19:52.383 --> 20:01.037
And so it's not too long before circumstances rise to challenge us, and our carefully constructed systems begin to show cracks.

20:01.057 --> 20:04.402
And pretty soon it's clear that the water is draining away.

20:04.802 --> 20:12.734
