22:38.405 --> 22:45.074
So that will carry over without understanding that we just need to hear from the Lord today.

22:45.378 --> 22:58.172
And today he's so multi-skilled and multifaceted that I can read the scripture that I've read a thousand times and he can tell me something different because I need to hear something different today.

22:58.232 --> 23:08.443
And so not so much time to read my Bible, not so much time to spend with the Lord, not so much time to go to church, not so much time to speak, keep on speaking life.

23:09.704 --> 23:15.250
When we try to keep our relationship with Jesus in a bucket instead of via direct

23:15.522 --> 23:16.143
connection.

23:16.583 --> 23:18.927
The water isn't alive anymore.

23:19.387 --> 23:20.168
It's stale.

23:21.570 --> 23:29.902
Jesus says, if anyone thirsts, let him come to me and drink and out of his very heart will flow rivers of living water like rivers.

23:30.583 --> 23:36.311
And again, he says, but the water that I give him will become in him a fountain.

23:36.331 --> 23:42.399
And Isaiah says, if you're thirsty, it doesn't matter if you're broke.

23:43.020 --> 23:44.242
Come to the water.

23:44.770 --> 23:48.174
It won't cost you anything except your life.

23:49.596 --> 24:00.869
It will cost you life because the very act of thirsting for living water all the time, every day, listen to me, flushes out every other thirst that is not of God.

24:01.690 --> 24:09.599
It flushes out all the impurities that have come in from how we live and where we live and who's around us and what's important to them.

24:09.619 --> 24:11.922
It flushes all that out.

24:12.578 --> 24:13.659
which is amazing.

24:13.800 --> 24:15.321
And so that's why it costs us our life.

24:15.662 --> 24:24.393
And that's why it's not a high price to pay because we don't want anything else because all those other things have been flushed away from out of our life.

24:24.533 --> 24:41.714
And so the more we thirst for living water, the less we thirst for things that aren't right for us, for movies that the Holy Spirit wouldn't want to watch with us, for company and relationships that bring division and fear and disagreement, the toxic

24:41.954 --> 24:54.755
fear-mongering that leads us to anxiety and panic, instead of this steadfast faith in the Christ who sets us free from all of that, and has called us to represent Him in the world that He has placed us in.

24:54.795 --> 25:01.746
And because we are surrounded now, everywhere we look, some people don't watch the news anymore because they just don't want to know.

25:01.806 --> 25:09.298
But I watch the news because I do want to know because God has called us to represent Him in a world that has lost its head.

25:09.666 --> 25:21.018
But this is the thing, it lost its head the day, those two beloved parents lost one beloved son because the other beloved son murdered him.

25:21.919 --> 25:23.381
From then, it's been crazy.

25:23.641 --> 25:28.086
From that point, there's been terrible, there's been terror and brokenness.

25:29.107 --> 25:35.154
Every generation of church is called to that place, to this world,

25:35.234 --> 25:40.667
to be Jesus in it, not to point the finger and say, not you, you're not allowed in.

25:41.029 --> 25:41.874
It's not that.

25:42.306 --> 25:45.830
Now, what we're called to is to be Jesus Christ.

25:45.850 --> 25:48.512
That means we can't afford to live in feedback loops.

25:48.572 --> 25:57.321
The only feedback loop that we can afford to live in is the one that comes from the living water, that rushes through us, that makes us know nobody's our enemy.

25:57.662 --> 25:59.343
God has called us to love our enemy.

25:59.604 --> 26:04.048
We have to speak the kingdom words into situations.

26:04.408 --> 26:09.874
And as we speak kingdom words in the kingdom situations, we are bringing kingdom

26:10.338 --> 26:11.460
We're bringing kingdom.

26:11.560 --> 26:19.030
It's so distressing to me to see the way the church has polarized itself and divided itself all across the world, choosing sides.

26:19.390 --> 26:23.956
When Jesus Christ didn't choose sides, He came to all of us.

26:24.517 --> 26:29.804
Every person on earth, every person ever born is created in the image of God.

26:29.864 --> 26:33.229
And Jesus came to all of those people.

26:33.750 --> 26:35.993
We divide ourselves off.

26:36.473 --> 26:39.858
We partition ourselves into different places.

26:40.290 --> 26:41.612
Jesus never did.

26:41.772 --> 26:42.393
And do you know what?

26:42.413 --> 26:43.835
The older and I've done that.

26:43.975 --> 26:48.782
I've partitioned off and I've pointed fingers and I've done a whole lot of those things.

26:49.803 --> 26:54.730
But the older I've become, the more I've understood Jesus did never do that.

26:55.231 --> 27:00.078
And if I'm a follower of Jesus and not just a Christian, I better not do it either.

27:00.779 --> 27:08.530
And so there's that thing that needs to take place in us because the toxic fear-mongering

27:08.706 --> 27:20.100
that is leading people in the church to anxiety and panic is actually a denial of who Jesus Christ is in our lives and what he has called us, how he has called us to represent him.

27:20.561 --> 27:28.230
Our source can only ever be Jesus Christ, no matter how elaborately we carve our systems and the lives that we developed.

27:28.651 --> 27:31.474
They may look and feel the same for a while

27:31.586 --> 28:01.106
But when we're living out of our own containers and drawing from the waters of our past experience and what we've studied and waters of a certain temperament and a habitual church life, when we're living out of waters that we've collected and stored rather than continuing a daily relationship with the living God, those containers will eventually crack and break from the pressure because we're not created to be able to live a godly life without God being there

28:01.186 --> 28:06.533
all the time, not just within our sphere, but today on the inside.

28:06.673 --> 28:10.998
And so bottles and jars cannot hold fountains and rivers.

28:11.559 --> 28:22.592
Living waters rush through our lives and they bring cleansing and purifying and refreshing and all that can only come from an up close and personal relationship with Jesus Christ.

28:22.633 --> 28:27.198
So it's not immediately obvious when someone is living out of their own system.

28:27.479 --> 28:30.322
Like we've all gotten away with it many times.

28:30.786 --> 28:32.628
but it's always obvious when they're not.

28:33.529 --> 28:42.639
Those mighty springs and fountains pour water, living water out of their lives, giving refreshment to everyone around.

28:43.780 --> 28:55.473
And those who get deep satisfaction from their own constant current relationship with Jesus Christ always become a channel of refreshing to the people around them.

28:56.074 --> 28:58.216
Everyone around them is refreshed.

28:58.556 --> 29:00.018
You spend time with them,

29:00.194 --> 29:11.466
and you walk away feeling valued and encouraged, and that God isn't working your life, and that no matter what things you may lose or may have lost, you can trust God to carry you through.

29:11.526 --> 29:12.968
Paul knew that.

29:13.468 --> 29:20.015
He says, Philippians three, verses eight and nine, what is more, I consider everything a loss.

29:20.876 --> 29:24.921
I don't know what it feels like to consider everything a loss.

29:25.802 --> 29:27.924
I mean, how does it feel?

29:28.304 --> 29:29.906
Like not a grief,

29:30.306 --> 29:35.072
grief-style loss, but like none of this is important kind of loss.

29:35.873 --> 29:45.364
What is more, I consider everything a loss because of the surpassing worth of knowing Christ Jesus, my Lord, for whose sake I have lost all things.

29:45.545 --> 29:54.536
I consider them garbage, that I may gain Christ and be found in Him, not having a righteousness of my own that comes from the law.

29:55.236 --> 29:59.762
Listen, I have been exhausted at times.

30:00.098 --> 30:03.783
trying to live in righteousness without drawing it from God.

30:03.924 --> 30:05.286
It's made me legalistic.

30:06.187 --> 30:09.171
It's made me, it's broken me.

30:10.573 --> 30:12.156
It's damaged other people.

30:13.217 --> 30:27.218
Not having a righteousness of my own, but that which comes through faith in Christ, the righteousness that comes from God on the basis of faith.

30:28.066 --> 30:30.169
Paul had worked very hard on his system.

30:30.789 --> 30:33.472
His role as a man of God was well-defined.

30:34.213 --> 30:38.298
People knew him as zealous and to uncompromising with God's law.

30:38.779 --> 30:41.302
He's a Pharisee among Pharisees.

30:41.943 --> 30:44.045
He's outstanding among his peers.

30:44.646 --> 30:49.111
He's a powerful man on his way to the top of the religious structure.

30:49.712 --> 30:54.898
And he built his system with great care, but it still broke.

30:56.898 --> 30:58.339
Paul could have tried to repair it.

30:59.521 --> 31:05.507
He could have tried to keep his reputation intact, make sure he kept his job and his title.

31:06.728 --> 31:07.249
But he didn't.

31:07.989 --> 31:08.770
He left it behind.

31:08.930 --> 31:17.639
He just got up and walked away from it all and directly into the arms of the author and the perfecter of his faith who is Jesus Christ.

31:18.640 --> 31:24.466
And as the years went on, when people went looking for Paul, they always knew where to find him.

31:25.314 --> 31:29.138
they found Paul in him, in Christ.

31:29.979 --> 31:42.591
No matter what the situation, no matter how hard his day or his year had been, this guy was whipped three separate times and each time it was 39 times.

31:44.032 --> 31:44.893
Can you imagine that?

31:45.914 --> 31:53.842
Can you imagine, just think about yourself enduring that for your faith in Christ and for the call on your life that

31:54.050 --> 31:55.853
God has given to you which we all have.

31:56.994 --> 32:17.182
When he was imprisoned for his faith, when he was betrayed by people who used to be his friends and his co-workers, when he was shipwrecked and floating more than 24 hours in the ocean and he's clinging to a piece of ship and he doesn't know if he's even going to get out of this or not.

32:17.202 --> 32:19.986
They always found Paul in Christ.

32:20.642 --> 32:25.327
because he had known what it was to develop and maintain a facade.

32:25.948 --> 32:31.914
Particular behaviors to impress people and impress God with his fervor and his godliness.

32:32.615 --> 32:41.565
And he suddenly realized how empty and broken and futile it all really was because it's just our system.

32:42.686 --> 32:49.714
When he realized where the source lay, when he found that living water, he left that old broken system in the dust.

32:50.178 --> 32:58.188
He left behind his reputation, his institutional power and authority, the admiration and the kudos that came from the people around him.

32:58.608 --> 33:03.874
He left behind the dignity and the comfort and the applause of people, and he embraced Christ.

33:03.995 --> 33:10.522
And in doing so, he become one of the greatest living testimonies to the power of Jesus Christ that we know.

33:10.563 --> 33:14.247
There are many others, but we haven't read their books.

33:14.708 --> 33:20.114
They've just lived and died over these past 2100 years, serving Christ with their lives.

33:20.226 --> 33:21.768
many who died of it.

33:23.370 --> 33:29.097
Being a Christian was never meant to be like everything's hunky dory and we're going to live happily ever after.

33:29.437 --> 33:36.306
Jesus never promised that, but the church somehow has put that forward as maybe being a sweetener to get people to come in.

33:36.546 --> 33:37.767
No, it's not about that.

33:38.128 --> 33:38.769
It costs.

33:39.610 --> 33:40.511
It costs.

33:41.252 --> 33:43.154
But it doesn't matter if it costs.

33:43.330 --> 33:47.937
if there's a direct connection to the living water that's washing all the impurities out.

33:48.237 --> 33:50.521
And the thing that says, no, I want to hold on to that.

33:50.921 --> 33:53.405
There've been things where I've thought, no, I want to hold on to that.

33:54.046 --> 33:56.329
But then you allow the living water to come.

33:56.750 --> 34:01.216
It just flushes all the impurities away because we all have impurities.

34:01.297 --> 34:13.074
And so he became a person out of him, flowed rivers and torrents and fountains of living water that have continued to refresh Christians 2000 years later.

34:13.826 --> 34:16.389
And you know, there are times when people come looking for us.

34:17.451 --> 34:19.593
They want to know what we're all about.

34:20.174 --> 34:24.219
How authentic are we when you scrape it right down to the surface?

34:24.860 --> 34:26.302
What's it like in the bad times?

34:26.402 --> 34:30.688
Because sometimes in the good times, we can just keep it all balanced and it's all okay.

34:30.708 --> 34:31.789
But how are you?

34:31.990 --> 34:34.333
How am I in the really bad times?

34:34.913 --> 34:38.578
You know, the good times disguise systems.

34:38.754 --> 34:44.202
but bad times make it so obvious whether we're living out of a cistern or springs of living water.

34:44.542 --> 34:46.064
So what do they see in here?

34:46.465 --> 34:48.568
Does anybody know where Bev is?

34:49.710 --> 34:54.056
Oh, she's over there in that shattered old cistern and she's screaming about all the rats and snakes.

34:54.757 --> 34:57.481
And we threw her a rope, but she says, no, she can work it out herself.

34:57.901 --> 34:58.883
She doesn't need help from you.

34:58.923 --> 35:03.008
She's trying to mend the cracks and she's praying for rain.

35:03.709 --> 35:05.131
I don't want that set of me.

35:05.151 --> 35:06.994
I want them to say,

35:08.322 --> 35:10.164
See where all that water's coming from?

35:10.204 --> 35:15.191
You can't actually see her, but if you follow the water, she's in him.

35:16.052 --> 35:17.674
I want that to be said about me.

35:17.794 --> 35:21.720
I've got a few years left still for it because she's in him.

35:21.760 --> 35:34.256
You'll find her in Christ when times are toughest, when she feels like no one cares about her, when she isn't the popular choice, when she's been overlooked or undervalued or betrayed by people that she loves.

35:34.617 --> 35:35.698
She's in Christ.

35:36.034 --> 35:37.395
That's how I want to be remembered.

35:37.476 --> 35:40.138
I don't want to be remembered as somebody important.

35:40.379 --> 35:42.441
I want to be remembered as somebody who's in Christ.

35:42.541 --> 35:48.868
And honestly, I'm not always that, but it's my aim and it's my fervent desire.

35:49.208 --> 36:05.266
And God keeps teaching me how to find my place in Him, not having a righteousness of my own from the system that I've created, but from the powerful flood of the Holy Spirit operating in my life, continually washing out all the junk that otherwise

36:05.506 --> 36:14.727
keeps coming in, driving me to performance and driving me to legalism and driving me to working out who can be excluded and who can be included.

36:14.788 --> 36:21.042
And it's only as we live our lives in him choosing to keep relying on his power and grace

36:21.122 --> 36:32.534
to refresh our lives rather than our own ability to contain what we were once given that we will experience those times of deep refreshing and get to live in those wild and wonderful rivers.

36:32.934 --> 36:35.016
And it's a relationship like any other.

36:35.377 --> 36:37.799
You don't have to do anything special.

36:37.959 --> 36:40.782
It just involves time and it has to be current.

36:41.183 --> 36:45.067
It must always be current, but we don't have to do anything special.

36:45.107 --> 36:46.468
Just be with him.

36:46.568 --> 36:48.210
Just be together with him.

36:48.322 --> 36:49.524
Stop where you are.

36:49.624 --> 36:51.086
It doesn't matter what you're doing.

36:51.346 --> 36:56.152
When you realize you're there, you can stop where you are and just say, Holy Spirit.

37:01.419 --> 37:02.640
I've lost that living water.

37:02.680 --> 37:04.963
I'm so sorry, Holy Spirit come.

37:06.105 --> 37:07.226
Just come to me again.

37:10.410 --> 37:11.151
And there he is.

37:12.953 --> 37:13.754
There he is.

37:13.935 --> 37:15.657
Like, that's mind blowing to me.

37:15.817 --> 37:16.658
I had a dad.

37:16.962 --> 37:18.264
It was always too busy.

37:20.186 --> 37:25.614
And that actually, you know, always felt like I needed to earn my place in there.

37:26.655 --> 37:36.188
But the Holy Spirit and our God, our Father, doesn't have to say, doesn't say to us, yeah, it's about time, finally.

37:36.228 --> 37:37.110
Okay.

37:37.690 --> 37:40.855
Well, just you sit there for a while and when I'm ready, I'm going to talk with you.

37:41.716 --> 37:42.677
He doesn't say that.

37:43.158 --> 37:46.162
It's like, yeah, come in.

37:46.274 --> 37:48.136
immediate, it's an immediate thing.

37:48.176 --> 37:52.320
We all are in the same boat.

37:52.800 --> 37:53.601
We're too busy.

37:53.801 --> 37:54.502
We're too tired.

37:54.562 --> 37:56.824
We're too distracted to spend time with him.

37:56.845 --> 38:03.411
But once we realize we've disconnected, it's so easy to come back, being found in him.

38:04.292 --> 38:10.478
Not having a righteousness of my own, which is from the law, but that which is true faith in Jesus Christ.

38:11.119 --> 38:14.482
That's our only way out of automatic pilot.

38:14.722 --> 38:16.565
into the water that's alive with Christ.

38:16.625 --> 38:24.576
And so the most powerful thing about this is that even though we do, like even if we do build systems, this is the astonishing thing.

38:25.257 --> 38:29.002
Even when we do build systems, they're not going to keep us out of heaven.

38:29.563 --> 38:30.425
That's a done deal.

38:31.105 --> 38:31.927
We're welcomed in.

38:32.327 --> 38:33.229
God welcomes us.

38:33.309 --> 38:34.270
He's like, come in.

38:34.330 --> 38:37.535
Don't bring your system with you, but you know, you can come in.

38:38.296 --> 38:42.642
It's not going to stop us from arriving into eternity.

38:42.754 --> 38:44.036
with Jesus Christ forever.

38:44.336 --> 38:45.998
No, it will not stop that.

38:47.260 --> 39:00.095
But drinking from the system that we created will never give us the rich, full satisfaction that we can experience from a daily connection with Jesus Christ through the power of His Holy Spirit.

39:00.696 --> 39:03.780
If I am bored with my life, pay attention to what I'm saying.

39:04.681 --> 39:11.890
If I'm bored with my life, my faith, my church, my ministry, if it all feels stale,

39:13.058 --> 39:16.664
It's often because I haven't realized how dehydrated I am.

39:16.684 --> 39:27.140
I'm doing all the same stuff, but without the richness of the one-on-one time with Jesus, and we can do all the right stuff on automatic pilot.

39:27.301 --> 39:30.105
And that is a common trap that we all fall into.

39:30.205 --> 39:32.609
And God doesn't hold it against us.

39:33.130 --> 39:35.594
He doesn't say, take a number and get in line.

39:36.195 --> 39:38.919
He doesn't say, sort your life out and then come back to me.

39:39.540 --> 39:40.882
No, he's immediately there.

39:42.306 --> 39:47.454
Unbelievably, we are now in the second quarter of the 21st century.

39:48.335 --> 39:51.961
We're in times of deep uncertainty and suspicion and fear.

39:52.822 --> 40:03.980
Jesus wants us to see things from his perspective, acknowledging the wrong, but not living in fear of it and not finding ways to make those, if we could just sort those people out, we'd be all right.

40:04.721 --> 40:06.103
We call to represent him.

40:06.724 --> 40:10.610
We call to represent him, not certain factions.

40:11.682 --> 40:30.025
Living out of the richness of a relationship with Jesus Christ is the only way that we will be able to maintain our inner peace and live in the joy that he promises will give us strength to face these days that are ahead of us.

40:32.027 --> 40:34.811
Don't ever say, oh, God's going to keep us from this.

40:35.051 --> 40:40.818
No, no, I remember, I remember putting my kids in a Christian school in high school and then

40:41.666 --> 40:57.370
they couldn't continue and so we had to put our kids in another school and and that happened a couple of times and then I remember they started they tried again and and one of the ladies that I knew she had a child in there and and she said well that's not going to happen to us though because God loves us too much.

40:58.231 --> 41:02.718
I'm like yeah well you know I'm always kind of thought he loved us as well so there is that.

41:03.499 --> 41:06.845
Listen there are people living and dying for their faith all over the world.

41:07.526 --> 41:10.450
There are people in desperate situations which

41:10.690 --> 41:18.861
You will know if you watch the news or read the news and watch it and read it with your hand over your heart and say, Lord, protect my heart as I read this.

41:19.302 --> 41:31.178
But don't ignore it because the church is never called to be in an ivory tower, trying to keep its beautiful white dress from getting muddied by the mud of the world.

41:31.218 --> 41:40.210
We are called, Jesus was incarnated into the world as a human being so that

41:40.450 --> 41:44.896
He could bring change and healing and restoration.

41:45.277 --> 41:46.578
And so is the church.

41:47.580 --> 41:49.783
So is every individual in the church.

41:49.883 --> 41:58.355
And so that's for us, Jesus wants us to see things from his perspective, acknowledging the wrong, but not living in the fear of it.

41:58.675 --> 42:01.439
We call to represent him and not certain factions.

42:01.820 --> 42:06.546
And so living out of that relationship is how we're going to minister and come

42:06.754 --> 42:09.878
into any context within a piece and live in that joy.

42:10.339 --> 42:15.386
It is the way that we're going to be able to face the challenges that this new era brings.

42:16.087 --> 42:21.895
Our good Christian life can so easily distract us from our relationship with Jesus.

42:23.297 --> 42:25.580
And so it's never too late to plug into the source.

42:26.702 --> 42:28.044
And let me just finish with this.

42:29.266 --> 42:32.370
Maybe you've never even begun a relationship with Jesus.

42:32.930 --> 42:38.596
Or maybe it's a way back there and it's been a while since you and he sat down together to have a chat.

42:39.857 --> 42:45.122
And that's okay because every one of us has either had to come to him or come back to him.

42:45.623 --> 42:46.324
That's okay.

42:46.364 --> 42:51.449
You know something's missing and you've tried so hard to make your life work.

42:52.350 --> 43:00.658
Today is a great day to begin a new adventure, having a relationship with Christ and having that terrible thirst

43:01.026 --> 43:07.435
that we often don't even know we have, but it's dog dust for so long, having it satisfied.

43:08.397 --> 43:15.627
And so if that's you, I know that afterwards there'll be prayer out here at the front, there will be people willing to pray for you.

43:15.728 --> 43:24.941
And if you're somebody that feels like, yeah, I need to begin the adventure or I need to begin it again, there's going to be people who are going to love to pray for you.

43:25.302 --> 43:28.306
And they don't think they're better than you because they've done it too.

43:29.954 --> 43:54.732
Father, in the name of Jesus, we stand together in you, not having a righteousness of our own, which comes from the law, from our systems, from the lives that we've tried to develop and build for ourselves, but from you, from Jesus Christ, the righteous one, not having a righteousness of our own, but that which is through faith in Jesus Christ.

43:55.934 --> 43:58.578
Lord, I pray that as we enter this

43:59.266 --> 44:05.415
dramatic new era that the world has come into.

44:05.435 --> 44:17.852
I ask for God that you will help us know what it is to represent you, the incarnation of God, who came to earth not to take sides, but to bring life.

44:19.014 --> 44:25.843
We pray that you will anoint us for remembering that when we get out of alignment.

44:26.484 --> 44:27.826
We can just come back again.

44:28.162 --> 44:30.952
knowing that you don't blame us, you just welcome us.

44:31.734 --> 44:33.179
So Lord, we're so grateful to You.

44:33.240 --> 44:37.555
I pray richness of blessing on this church in Jesus' name.

44:38.056 --> 44:38.578
Amen.

